00:25:37.320 --> 00:25:38.700
SPEAKER: Yeah, the
New York version.

00:25:38.700 --> 00:25:41.116
MICHAEL SOLOMONOV: You got to
make sure the coffee is hot,

00:25:41.116 --> 00:25:43.290
so you can shoot it down
your throat, you know?

00:25:43.290 --> 00:25:44.220
SPEAKER: All right.

00:25:44.220 --> 00:25:46.290
Food competition.

00:25:46.290 --> 00:25:49.309
So what's your favorite food
destination besides Israel?

00:25:49.309 --> 00:25:51.600
MICHAEL SOLOMONOV: I think
that we live in this great--

00:25:51.600 --> 00:25:53.310
this is a frustrating,
stupid-ass answer

00:25:53.310 --> 00:25:54.434
that I'm going to give you.

00:25:54.434 --> 00:25:56.070
But I think that
everywhere right now

00:25:56.070 --> 00:25:57.580
is like a foodie town.

00:25:57.580 --> 00:26:03.680
And I think that we are
on the cusp of people

00:26:03.680 --> 00:26:05.810
really getting a chance
to express themselves

00:26:05.810 --> 00:26:07.010
and where they're from.

00:26:07.010 --> 00:26:11.420
And although there's tons
of xenophobia and alienation

00:26:11.420 --> 00:26:13.550
happening all over
the world, people now

00:26:13.550 --> 00:26:17.354
have this grassroots way
of telling their story.

00:26:17.354 --> 00:26:18.770
And I think that
everywhere you go

00:26:18.770 --> 00:26:21.830
has got these
immigrant populations.

00:26:21.830 --> 00:26:23.540
Everywhere you go
in the world have

00:26:23.540 --> 00:26:25.790
got people that have
made this living

00:26:25.790 --> 00:26:29.460
generation after generation from
preparing food and hospitality.

00:26:29.460 --> 00:26:32.000
So I like going anywhere.

00:26:32.000 --> 00:26:33.230
I like going anywhere.

00:26:33.230 --> 00:26:36.200
I like going in holes in
the walls in any city.

00:26:36.200 --> 00:26:37.130
I think it's amazing.

00:26:37.130 --> 00:26:38.838
We were just talking
about South Florida.

00:26:38.838 --> 00:26:41.980
And when I learned
how to cook, I

00:26:41.980 --> 00:26:44.200
went to culinary school
in West Palm Beach.

00:26:44.200 --> 00:26:46.900
And there were three kinds
of restaurants there.

00:26:46.900 --> 00:26:50.530
And now you can go
anywhere and figure out

00:26:50.530 --> 00:26:51.970
where people are from.

00:26:51.970 --> 00:26:56.740
You can go to any
random road in Florida,

00:26:56.740 --> 00:26:59.110
and just take it, and
find a little place

00:26:59.110 --> 00:27:02.020
that has arepas, or
the best Cuban coffee,

00:27:02.020 --> 00:27:05.230
or great Thai food.

00:27:05.230 --> 00:27:06.430
And it's just--

00:27:06.430 --> 00:27:07.090
I don't know.

00:27:07.090 --> 00:27:09.760
I don't think there's a place
in the country that doesn't

00:27:09.760 --> 00:27:12.100
have a great food scene.

00:27:12.100 --> 00:27:15.370
I don't often eat at
fancy restaurants,

00:27:15.370 --> 00:27:17.620
mostly because I can't sit
for more than 45 minutes

00:27:17.620 --> 00:27:19.540
without having an
anxiety attack.

00:27:19.540 --> 00:27:23.259
But I think that--

00:27:23.259 --> 00:27:23.800
I don't know.

00:27:23.800 --> 00:27:25.390
I think anywhere
is pretty great.

00:27:25.390 --> 00:27:26.110
SPEAKER: Yeah.

00:27:26.110 --> 00:27:27.568
MICHAEL SOLOMONOV:
Anywhere Queens.

00:27:27.568 --> 00:27:30.910
I just get on a
train and go out.

